      "author": "nazdridoy",
      "description": "## What's Changed in v1.5.0\r\n\r\nThis release introduces **Adaptive Study Mode**, a major update designed to personalize your learning experience by prioritizing the areas where you need the most practice.\r\n\r\n### Highlights\r\n\r\n*   **Intelligent Adaptive Study**: A new mode that analyzes your past performance to serve a personalized mix of questions.\r\n*   **Mastery Tracking**: Visualize your progress with new performance metrics and category-based mastery badges.\r\n*   **Enhanced Performance Insights**: A dedicated summary panel to track your improvement over time.\r\n\r\n### What's Changed\r\n\r\n*   **Adaptive Learning Engine**: Implemented smart categorization and selection logic that focuses on your weak points while maintaining your strengths through a customizable \"adaptive mix ratio.\"\r\n*   **Visual Performance Metrics**: Added a new performance summary panel to the landing page and detailed mastery improvement metrics to the results view, helping you see exactly how much you've improved.\r\n*   **Enhanced History Management**: Improved the way study history is stored and managed, resulting in better performance and more efficient data storage.\r\n*   **UI/UX Refinements**: Introduced category badges and specialized styling for mastery progress to provide clearer visual feedback on your study goals.\r\n*   **Customizable Settings**: Added an adaptive mix ratio slider to the settings tab, allowing you to fine-tune the balance between new and review material.\r\n\r\n### Full Changelog\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/nazdridoy/obsidian-cbt-exam/compare/1.4.1...1.5.0",
